Analysis of the Main Target Image  
• Block Count and Layers  
  – There are 6 total blocks.  
  – They form 4 vertical “layers”:  
     1) Bottom layer: a red arch on the left and a tall orange cylinder on the right.  
     2) Second layer: a green rectangular block resting on top of the arch.  
     3) Third layer: a blue cube stacked on top of the green block (while the cylinder continues upward).  
     4) Top layer: an orange triangular roof piece on the blue cube and another identical roof piece on the top of the cylinder.  

• Spatial Arrangement  
  – The red arch (left) and the orange cylinder (right) sit side by side on the ground.  
  – A single green rectangular prism spans the top of the arch.  
  – Above the green block, the blue cube is centered.  
  – Both the cube and cylinder receive an orange roof piece of the same orientation.  

Selection of Required Blocks (matching shape/orientation exactly from the dictionary)  
• Red arch with front opening: index 1  
• Green rectangular prism (horizontal): index 11  
• Blue cube: index 6  
• Orange cylinder (vertical): index 12  
• Orange roof wedge (two copies, same orientation): index 15 (used twice)  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 12  
  Step3: Move block with index 11  
  Step4: Move block with index 6  
  Step5: Move block with index 15  
  Step6: Move block with index 15  
}
